[{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_1","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":1,"text":"And it came to pass in the day in which Moses finished the setting-up of the tabernacle, that he anointed it, and consecrated it, and all its furniture, and the altar and all its furniture, he even anointed them, and consecrated them.","searchKeywords":["and","came","pass","the","day","which","moses","finished","setting","tabernacle","that","anointed","consecrated","all","its","furniture","altar","even","them"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_2","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":2,"text":"And the princes of Israel brought , twelve princes of their fathers' houses: these were the heads of tribes, these are they that presided over the numbering.","searchKeywords":["and","the","princes","israel","brought","twelve","their","fathers","houses","these","were","heads","tribes","are","they","that","presided","over","numbering"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_3","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":3,"text":"And they brought their gift before the Lord, six covered waggons, and twelve oxen; a waggon from two princes, and a calf from each: and they brought them before the tabernacle.","searchKeywords":["and","they","brought","their","gift","before","the","lord","six","covered","waggons","twelve","oxen","waggon","from","two","princes","calf","each","them","tabernacle"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_4","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":4,"text":"And the Lord spoke to Moses, saying,","searchKeywords":["and","the","lord","spoke","moses","saying"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_5","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":5,"text":"Take of them, and they shall be for the works of the services of the tabernacle of witness: and thou shalt give them to the Levites, to each one according to his ministration.","searchKeywords":["take","them","and","they","shall","for","the","works","services","tabernacle","witness","thou","shalt","give","levites","each","one","according","his","ministration"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_6","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":6,"text":"And Moses took the waggons and the oxen, and gave them to the Levites.","searchKeywords":["and","moses","took","the","waggons","oxen","gave","them","levites"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_7","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":7,"text":"And he gave two waggons and four oxen to the sons of Gedson, according to their ministrations.","searchKeywords":["and","gave","two","waggons","four","oxen","the","sons","gedson","according","their","ministrations"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_8","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":8,"text":"And four waggons and eight oxen he gave to the sons of Merari according to their ministrations, by Ithamar the son of Aaron the priest.","searchKeywords":["and","four","waggons","eight","oxen","gave","the","sons","merari","according","their","ministrations","ithamar","son","aaron","priest"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_9","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":9,"text":"But to the sons of Caath he gave them not, because they have the ministrations of the sacred things: they shall bear them on their shoulders.","searchKeywords":["but","the","sons","caath","gave","them","not","because","they","have","ministrations","sacred","things","shall","bear","their","shoulders"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_10","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":10,"text":"And the rulers brought for the dedication of the altar, in the day in which he anointed it, and the rulers brought their gifts before the altar.","searchKeywords":["and","the","rulers","brought","for","dedication","altar","day","which","anointed","their","gifts","before"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_11","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":11,"text":"And the Lord said to Moses, One chief each day, they shall offer their gifts a chief each day for the dedication of the altar.","searchKeywords":["and","the","lord","said","moses","one","chief","each","day","they","shall","offer","their","gifts","for","dedication","altar"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_12","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":12,"text":"And he that offered his gift on the first day, was Naasson the son of Aminadab, prince of the tribe of Juda.","searchKeywords":["and","that","offered","his","gift","the","first","day","was","naasson","son","aminadab","prince","tribe","juda"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_13","translationId":"brenton","testament":"OT","bookIndex":4,"bookName":"Numbers","bookAbbrev":"numbers","chapter":7,"verse":13,"text":"And he brought his gift, one silver charger of a hundred and thirty shekels was its weight, one silver bowl, of seventy shekels according to the holy shekel; both full of fine flour kneaded with oil for a meat-offering.","searchKeywords":["and","brought","his","gift","one","silver","charger","hundred","thirty","shekels","was","its","weight","bowl","seventy","according","the","holy","shekel","both","full","fine","flour","kneaded","with","oil","for","meat","offering"]},{"verseId":"brenton_numbers_7_14","t